<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=5 WIDTH=90%><TR><TD></TD><TD><CENTER><H1>Chapter    
11</H1></CENTER></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V1><H4>1</H4></TD><TD><P>  
In YHVH put I my trust: how say ye to my soul, Flee as a bird to your           
mountain?</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V2><H4>2</H4></TD><TD><P>For, 
lo, the wicked bend their bow, they make ready their arrow upon the string,     
that they may privily shoot at the upright in heart.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD       
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V3><H4>3</H4></TD><TD><P>If the foundations be destroyed,    
what can the righteous do?</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V4><H4>4</H4>
</TD><TD><P>YHVH is in his holy temple, YHVH's throne is in heaven: his eyes    
behold, his eyelids try, the children of men.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP>  
<A NAME=V5><H4>5</H4></TD><TD><P>YHVH trieth the righteous: but the wicked and  
him that loveth violence his soul hateth.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A    
NAME=V6><H4>6</H4></TD><TD><P>Upon the wicked he shall rain snares, fire and    
brimstone, and an horrible tempest: this shall be the portion of their cup.</P> 
</TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V7><H4>7</H4></TD><TD><P>For the righteous 
YHVH loveth righteousness; his countenance doth behold the upright.</P></TD>    
